Mark is a unique blend of business person & programmer and has been transforming data into actionable results for six years. He accepts challenges and projects in the workplace as a means for growth and exudes a strong passion for all things data, analytics and risk. As an astute modeler, he utilizes SQL, SSRS/SSIS, Visual Studio, advanced Excel (VBA, PowerPivot & DAX) and R Studio to create solutions to real business problems including interactive dashboards, data mining, credit scoring, behavioral and segmentation modeling and general financing modeling. Mark has successfully led projects from start to finish including small cap M&A (debt financing); corporate loan origination & refinancing; predictive scoring models; mark-to-market cash flow valuations; and automated loan origination analysis and implementation. Mark currently attends UC Irvine for a specialization in Data Analytics expecting completion in January 2019.
